          code review, issue tracking, or team collaboration built around
          version control; or
      (b) is derived from, inspired by, or functionally equivalent to the
          Software in its core features, architecture, data model, or user
          experience.

1.7 "Derivative Work" means any work, regardless of form or medium, that:
      (a) incorporates, is based on, or is derived from all or any portion of
          the Software's source code, compiled output, structure, architecture,
          sequence, or organization;
      (b) constitutes a functional clone, port, translation, adaptation, or
          rewrite of the Software or any substantial part thereof, even if no
          original source code is copied verbatim;
      (c) replicates the look, feel, user interface design, data model,
          database schema, or API design of the Software in substantial part;
      (d) is produced by automated transformation, compilation, decompilation,
          reverse engineering, or code generation from the Software; or
      (e) is trained upon, summarized from, or materially assisted in creation
          by any AI system, language model, or automated tool that was itself
          trained on or given access to the Software's source code.
    For the avoidance of doubt, "substantial similarity" under copyright law
    is the operative standard; verbatim copying is not required.

1.8 "Rebranding" means presenting the Software or any Derivative Work under
    any name, logo, domain, trademark, or brand identity other than "SigmaGit"
    — or stripping the SigmaGit identity — while retaining substantially the
